               <head/>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Kulliyāt-i ʿUrfī by Muḥammad ʿUrfī Shīrāzī</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  <msItem class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh89005046" n="1" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_51-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20212">Kulliyāt-i ʿUrfī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20212">کلیات عرفی</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658492.0x000001 viaf_50413291">Muḥammad ʿUrfī Shīrāzī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_50413291">محمد عرفی شبرازی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">ای متاع درد در بازار جان انداخته</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">شمع جمال خویش که دانا دوش... جمال خویش</explicit>
                     <note>
                        <p>Due to wear-and-tear, parts of the manuscript are illegible, including a part of the explicit. </p>
                        <p>The manuscript is made up of different sections, occasionally with individual headpieces (e.g. f86v, f272v, f299v). Ff1-85r, qaṣīdahs; ff86v-213, ghazals followed by rubāʿiyyāt until f227r; between f227v and f272r, Majmūʿ al-Akbar; Kitāb-i Khusraw va Shīrīn ff272v-285v; between ff286v-298v, muqaṭṭaʿāt; ff299v-303v prose. The manuscript ends abruptly in the middle of one of these prose pieces. </p>
                        <p>There are several seals on the title pages of the individual sections (e.g. f85v-86r, f286r) before the new headpieces. All of these have been effaced or have faded away into total illegibility. </p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
